1.png" height=3D"610" width=3D"912"></p></div></div><h3 class=3D"title" id=
=3D"SegmentLungsFrom3DChestScanExample-2">Segment the Lungs</h3><p>Segment =
the lungs in the CT scan data using the active contour technique. Active co=
ntours is a region growing algorithm which requires initial seed points. Th=
e example uses the Image Segmenter app to create this seed mask by segmenti=
ng two orthogonal 2-D slices, one in the XY plane and the other in the XZ p=
lane. The example then inserts these two segmentations into a 3-D mask. The=
 example passes this mask to the <a href=3D"https://ww2.mathworks.cn/help/r=
eleases/R2023b/images/ref/activecontour.html" data-docid=3D"images_ref#btue=
p4x-1" class=3D"a"><code class=3D"olink">activecontour</code></a> function =
to create a 3-D segmentation of the lungs in the chest cavity. (This exampl=
e uses the active contour method but you could use other segmentation techn=
iques to accomplish the same goal, such as flood-fill.)</p><p>Extract the c=
enter slice in both the XY and XZ dimensions.</p><div class=3D"code_respons=
ive -has_code_copy"><div class=3D"programlisting"><div class=3D"codeinput">=
<div class=3D"btn-group code_actions"> <button type=3D"button" class=3D"btn=
