/span></span></button></span></div></li></ul></div><pre>BW =3D XY &gt; 0.50=
98;</pre></div></div></div><p>After this initial lung segmentation, clean u=
p the mask using options on the <strong class=3D"emphasis bold">Refine Mask=
</strong> menu. </p><div class=3D"informalfigure"><div id=3D"d126e29390" cl=
ass=3D"mediaobject"><p><img src=3D"https://ww2.mathworks.cn/help/releases/R=
2023b/examples/images/win64/SegmentLungsFrom3DChestScanExample_03.png" heig=
ht=3D"349" width=3D"592"></p></div></div><p>In the app, you can click each =
option to invert the mask image so that the lungs are in the foreground (<s=
trong class=3D"emphasis bold">Invert Mask</strong>), remove other segmented=
 elements besides the lungs (<strong class=3D"emphasis bold">Clear Borders<=
/strong>), and fill holes inside the lung segmentation (<strong class=3D"em=
phasis bold">Fill Holes</strong>). Finally, use the <strong class=3D"emphas=
is bold">Morphology</strong> option to smooth the edges of the lung segment=
ation. On the Morphology tab, select the <strong class=3D"emphasis bold">Er=
ode Mask</strong> operation. After performing these steps, select <strong c=
lass=3D"emphasis bold">Show Binary</strong> and save the mask image to the =
workspace. </p><p>The app executes the following code to refine the mask.</=
p><div class=3D"code_responsive -has_code_copy"><div class=3D"programlistin=
g"><div class=3D"codeinput"><div class=3D"btn-group code_actions"> <button =
type=3D"button" class=3D"btn btn-default dropdown-toggle" data-toggle=3D"dr=
opdown" aria-haspopup=3D"true" aria-expanded=3D"false"> <span class=3D"copy=
_code_popover_target" id=3D"copy_popover_07"><span class=3D"icon-copy" id=
=3D"copy_popover_07"></span> Get <span class=3D"caret" id=3D"copy_popover_0=
7"></span></span></button><ul class=3D"dropdown-menu dropdown-menu-right co=
py_code"><li class=3D"copy_code_block"><button id=3D"copyBlock07"><span cla=
ss=3D"icon-copy"></span> Copy Code Block</button></li><li role=3D"separator=
" aria-hidden=3D"true" class=3D"divider"></li><li class=3D"copy_code_openex=
ample"><p><span class=3D"icon-webinar"></span> Copy openExample Command<br>=
<small>Paste command in MATLAB to download and open example files</small></=
p><div role=3D"presentation" class=3D"input-group"><input type=3D"text" cla=
ss=3D"form-control" readonly=3D"" value=3D"openExample('images/SegmentLungs=
From3DChestScanExample')"><span class=3D"input-group-btn"><button class=3D"=
btn btn_color_blue" type=3D"button" id=3D"copyCommand07"><span class=3D"ico=
n-copy"><span class=3D"sr-only">Copy</span></span></button></span></div></l=
i></ul></div><pre>BW =3D imcomplement(BW);
BW =3D imclearborder(BW);
BW =3D imfill(BW, <span style=3D"color:#A020F0">"holes"</span>);
radius =3D 3;
decomposition =3D 0;
se =3D strel(<span style=3D"color:#A020F0">"disk"</span>,radius,decompositi=
on);
BW =3D imerode(BW, se);
maskedImageXY =3D XY;
maskedImageXY(~BW) =3D 0;
imshow(maskedImageXY)</pre></div></div></div><div class=3D"informalfigure">=
<div id=3D"d126e29418" class=3D"mediaobject"><p><img src=3D"https://ww2.mat=
hworks.cn/help/releases/R2023b/examples/images/win64/SegmentLungsFrom3DChes=
tScanExample_04.png" width=3D"399"></p></div></div><p>Perform the same oper=
ation on the XZ slice. Using Load Image, select the <code class=3D"literal"=
>XZ</code> variable. Use thresholding to perform the initial segmentation o=
f the lungs. For the XZ slice, the <strong class=3D"emphasis bold">Global T=
hreshold</strong> option creates an adequate segmentation (the call to <cod=
e class=3D"literal">imbinarize</code> in the following code). As with the X=
Y slice, use options on the <strong class=3D"emphasis bold">Refine Mask</st=
rong> menu to create a polished segmentation of the lungs. In the erosion o=
peration on the Morphology tab, specify a radius of 13 to remove small extr=
aneous objects.</p><p>To segment the XZ slice and polish the result, the ap=
p executes the following code.</p><div class=3D"code_responsive -has_code_c=
opy"><div class=3D"programlisting"><div class=3D"codeinput"><div class=3D"b=
tn-group code_actions"> <button type=3D"button" class=3D"btn btn-default dr=
opdown-toggle" data-toggle=3D"dropdown" aria-haspopup=3D"true" aria-expande=
d=3D"false"> <span class=3D"copy_code_popover_target" id=3D"copy_popover_08=
"><span class=3D"icon-copy" id=3D"copy_popover_08"></span> Get <span class=
=3D"caret" id=3D"copy_popover_08"></span></span></button><ul class=3D"dropd=
own-menu dropdown-menu-right copy_code"><li class=3D"copy_code_block"><butt=
on id=3D"copyBlock08"><span class=3D"icon-copy"></span> Copy Code Block</bu=
tton></li><li role=3D"separator" aria-hidden=3D"true" class=3D"divider"></l=
i><li class=3D"copy_code_openexample"><p><span class=3D"icon-webinar"></spa=
n> Copy openExample Command<br><small>Paste command in MATLAB to download a=
nd open example files</small></p><div role=3D"presentation" class=3D"input-=
