ll></p><div role=3D"presentation" class=3D"input-group"><input type=3D"text=
" class=3D"form-control" readonly=3D"" value=3D"openExample('images/Segment=
LungsFrom3DChestScanExample')"><span class=3D"input-group-btn"><button clas=
s=3D"btn btn_color_blue" type=3D"button" id=3D"copyCommand011"><span class=
=3D"icon-copy"><span class=3D"sr-only">Copy</span></span></button></span></=
div></li></ul></div><pre>volumeViewer(segmentedImage)</pre></div></div></di=
v><p>By manipulating the alphamap settings in the Rendering Editor, you can=
 get a good view of just the lungs.</p><div class=3D"informalfigure"><div i=
d=3D"d126e29469" class=3D"mediaobject"><p><img src=3D"https://ww2.mathworks=
.cn/help/releases/R2023b/examples/images/win64/SegmentLungsFrom3DChestScanE=
xample_06.png" height=3D"695" width=3D"1188"></p></div></div><h3 class=3D"t=
itle" id=3D"SegmentLungsFrom3DChestScanExample-4">Compute the Volume of the=
 Segmented Lungs</h3><p>Use the <a href=3D"https://ww2.mathworks.cn/help/re=
leases/R2023b/images/ref/regionprops3.html" data-docid=3D"images_ref#mw_bf3=
9ad76-898e-415b-837b-f1d109d3f1be" class=3D"a"><code class=3D"olink">region=
props3</code></a> function with the "<code class=3D"literal">volume"</code>=
 option to calculate the volume of the lungs.</p><div class=3D"code_respons=
ive -has_code_copy"><div class=3D"programlisting"><div class=3D"codeinput">=
<div class=3D"btn-group code_actions"> <button type=3D"button" class=3D"btn=
